{
  "dialogueGraphs": [
    {
      "id": "DG_SIGNPOST_CONFLICT",
      "sceneId": "SCN-004",
      "startNodeId": "NARR_01",
      "nodes": [
        {
          "id": "NARR_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The signpost by the gate has been updated the way budgets get updated: by layering new certainty on top of old.",
          "next": "NARR_02"
        },
        {
          "id": "NARR_02",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Three plates. Two agencies. One post.\nThe bolts don\u2019t match.",
          "next": "NARR_03"
        },
        {
          "id": "NARR_03",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Top plate: DECOMMISSIONED \u2014 NO ENTRY \u2014 EFFECTIVE 09/14/2003. The logo is sun-faded into an unrecognizable municipal shape.\nMiddle plate: OPERATIONAL SITE \u2014 AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY \u2014 EFFECTIVE 05/02/2011. The seal is crisp. Different department name.\nBottom placard, smaller, apologetic: FOLLOW POSTED INSTRUCTIONS AS APPLICABLE.",
          "next": "NARR_04"
        },
        {
          "id": "NARR_04",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A phone number on the oldest plate has too few digits. It is printed confidently anyway.",
          "next": "MENU_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "MENU_01",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "LOOK_READ",
              "text": "look: Read it again.",
              "next": "NARR_READ_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "ASK_GOVERNS",
              "text": "ask: Which one governs?",
              "next": "PLY_GOVERNS_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "ASK_UPDATE",
              "text": "ask: Why update a decommissioned site?",
              "next": "PLY_UPDATE_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "TALK_RECORD",
              "text": "talk: Record what I\u2019m seeing.",
              "next": "PLY_RECORD_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "NARR_LEAVE_01"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "NARR_READ_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You track the dates with your thumb like they might line up if you press hard enough.\nThey do not.",
          "next": "NARR_READ_02"
        },
        {
          "id": "NARR_READ_02",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The post remains unanimous about one thing: it will not be responsible.",
          "next": "MENU_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "PLY_GOVERNS_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Which sign governs access?",
          "next": "NARR_GOVERNS_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "NARR_GOVERNS_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "There is no answer posted.\nThe post is an argument without a referee.",
          "next": "NARR_GOVERNS_02"
        },
        {
          "id": "NARR_GOVERNS_02",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The newer plate is mounted over the older one, but not centered, as if it wanted to be seen without touching responsibility.",
          "next": "MENU_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "PLY_UPDATE_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Why update a decommissioned site?",
          "next": "NARR_UPDATE_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "NARR_UPDATE_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Someone needed the word \u201cOPERATIONAL\u201d to exist here.\nSomeone else needed \u201cDECOMMISSIONED\u201d not to disappear.",
          "next": "NARR_UPDATE_02"
        },
        {
          "id": "NARR_UPDATE_02",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The bottom placard tries to split the difference, which is a form of optimism.",
          "next": "MENU_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "PLY_RECORD_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Log it as a conflict.",
          "next": "MENU_RECORD_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "MENU_RECORD_01",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "TALK_FORMAL",
              "text": "talk: Contradictory signage. Decommissioned versus operational.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "olea.protocolAssurance",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": true
                }
              ],
              "next": "NARR_FORMAL_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "TALK_INFORMAL",
              "text": "talk: Note: signs disagree.",
              "next": "NARR_INFORMAL_01"
            },
            {
              "id": "LEAVE_RECORD_BACK",
              "text": "leave: Back.",
              "next": "MENU_01"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "NARR_INFORMAL_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You jot it down in neutral language that won\u2019t start a war on its own.\nThe post continues to look official in three directions at once.",
          "next": "NARR_INFORMAL_02"
        },
        {
          "id": "NARR_INFORMAL_02",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You can keep it informal, or you can make it someone\u2019s problem on purpose.",
          "next": "MENU_01"
        },
        {
          "id": "NARR_FORMAL_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You take the photo straight-on, then from the side to catch the bolt pattern.\nYour hands stay steady; your jaw doesn\u2019t.",
          "next": "NARR_FORMAL_02"
        },
        {
          "id": "NARR_FORMAL_02",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "In your closure notes, you write it the way an auditor likes:\nCOMPLIANCE CONFLICT: Site status signage inconsistent across posting authorities and effective dates. Requires resolution prior to closure sign-off.",
          "next": "NARR_FORMAL_03"
        },
        {
          "id": "NARR_FORMAL_03",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You add a to-do: Resolve signage conflict (decommissioned vs operational).\nIt feels like feeding a machine that runs on paper.",
          "next": "END_LOG_OUTCOME"
        },
        {
          "id": "END_LOG_OUTCOME",
          "type": "end",
          "outcomeId": "log_signage_conflict_detail",
          "effects": [
            {
              "key": "compliance.signConflictInspected",
              "action": "set",
              "value": true
            },
            {
              "key": "paperwork.toDo",
              "action": "add",
              "value": "Resolve signage conflict (decommissioned vs operational)."
            },
            {
              "key": "compliance.flags",
              "action": "add",
              "value": "SIGNAGE_CONFLICT"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "NARR_LEAVE_01",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You leave the signpost to continue being right in incompatible ways.",
          "next": "END_NO_OUTCOME"
        },
        {
          "id": "END_NO_OUTCOME",
          "type": "end"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
